This is a mirror of http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=5095

CodeKit.vim provides support for controlling CodeKit 2 from Vim. It uses
CodeKit's AppleScript interface to provide the following features:

* Add the current project to CodeKit
* Switch to the current file's project
* Preview the current project in a browser
* Pause and unpause CodeKit's watching of project files

See `:help codekit` for a list of the provided commands.

Git repository and issue tracker available at: https://github.com/noahfrederick/vim-codekit
